description:
Replace the current typed formatting path in ChatAdapter with CompiledSignature rendering.

Location: crates/dspy-rs/src/adapter/chat.rs

Current flow (to be replaced):
- format_user_message_typed converts input to BamlValue
- Calls format_baml_value_for_prompt_typed for each field
- Uses field_spec.format for per-field formatting

New flow:
```rust
impl ChatAdapter {
    /// Format system message using CompiledSignature (typed, primary API)
    pub fn format_system_message<S: Signature>(&self) -> Result<String, RenderError> {
        let compiled = S::compile();
        compiled.render_messages(&Default::default())  // dummy input for system
            .map(|m| m.system)
    }

    /// Format user message using CompiledSignature (typed, primary API)
    pub fn format_user_message<S: Signature>(&self, input: &S::Input) -> Result<String, RenderError> {
        let compiled = S::compile();
        compiled.render_messages(input)
            .map(|m| m.user)
    }

    /// Format demo example
    pub fn format_demo<S: Signature>(&self, demo: S) -> Result<(String, String), RenderError> {
        let compiled = S::compile();
        let user = compiled.render_messages(&demo.input())?.user;
        // Output formatting...
        todo!()
    }
}
```

API naming:
- Drop the _typed suffix - typed API is now primary
- Rename old untyped to format_user_message_untyped (internal/private)
